00:16:16,034 --> 00:16:18,034
Just what do you mean?

273
00:16:18,034 --> 00:16:20,334
It's not true that Mr. Kurumatani coincidentally happened

274
00:16:20,334 --> 00:16:23,834
to run into Mr. Hayamizu at the convenience store.

275
00:16:23,834 --> 00:16:26,634
Just... just what do you think you're saying?

276
00:16:26,634 --> 00:16:28,734
Just a while ago,

277
00:16:28,734 --> 00:16:31,634
the boy I came with saw the ashtray in your car,

278
00:16:31,634 --> 00:16:34,434
and told me that it was full of cigarette butts.

279
00:16:35,634 --> 00:16:37,534
That's strange,

280
00:16:37,534 --> 00:16:40,834
because you don't seem to smoke.

281
00:16:40,834 --> 00:16:42,234
Well, that's...

282
00:16:42,234 --> 00:16:45,334
The brand name of that cigarette is called Paradise

283
00:16:45,334 --> 00:16:49,834
and moreover, the filter of all the cigarette butts were bitten flat.

284
00:16:49,834 --> 00:16:54,234
I mean it's the same as the cigarette butts that were thrown away

285
00:16:54,234 --> 00:16:57,334
by Mr. Hayamizu in front of the convenience store.

286
00:16:57,334 --> 00:16:59,934
In other words, Mr. Hayamizu drove the green car

287
00:16:59,934 --> 00:17:03,634
up to that convenience store.

288
00:17:03,634 --> 00:17:05,234
It's most likely that

289
00:17:05,234 --> 00:17:08,534
you lent the green car to Mr. Hayamizu

290
00:17:08,534 --> 00:17:12,234
while he was having his car tuned up at the factory.

291
00:17:12,234 --> 00:17:15,834
And isn't it that you promised to meet Mr. Hayamizu

292
00:17:15,834 --> 00:17:18,234
at the convenience store after tune-up was done

293
00:17:18,234 --> 00:17:20,834
to exchange his car for the green car that you lent him?

294
00:17:20,834 --> 00:17:23,434
Then you pretended to have a collision with Mr. Hayamizu

295
00:17:23,434 --> 00:17:25,434
and killed him, right?

296
00:17:25,434 --> 00:17:28,134
Just what are you talking about, Mr. Mouri?

297
00:17:28,134 --> 00:17:31,334
In other words, Mr. Kurumatani was planning

298
00:17:31,334 --> 00:17:35,334
to collide with Mr. Hayamizu's car to begin with.

299
00:17:35,334 --> 00:17:37,334
Don't be ridiculous!

300
00:17:37,334 --> 00:17:39,834
I'm hurt too, you know!

301
00:17:39,834 --> 00:17:41,734
One mistake, and I may have been dead too.

302
00:17:41,734 --> 00:17:43,834
No worry about that with your car,

303
00:17:43,834 --> 00:17:50,334
because it's equipped with iron pipe grill guard.

304
00:17:50,334 --> 00:17:53,134
Getting hurt would make it look even more like an accident

305
00:17:53,134 --> 00:17:55,634
and is better for you, isn't it?

306
00:17:55,634 --> 00:17:57,034
Making up stories!

307
00:17:57,034 --> 00:18:00,234
It's an accident that was caused by the collision course!

308
00:18:00,234 --> 00:18:03,334
The fact that there were no traces of the other driver

309
00:18:03,334 --> 00:18:05,434
stepping on the brakes is proof, isn't it?

310
00:18:05,434 --> 00:18:06,634
True.

311
00:18:06,634 --> 00:18:09,334
Mr. Mouri, I think it would be difficult

312
00:18:09,334 --> 00:18:11,234
to cause this phenomenon deliberately.

313
00:18:11,234 --> 00:18:14,234
The fact that Mr. Hayamizu didn't step on the brakes

314
00:18:14,234 --> 00:18:17,234
is not because of the collision course phenomenon.

315
00:18:18,734 --> 00:18:20,434
Mr. Kurumatani rigged it,

316
00:18:20,434 --> 00:18:24,734
so that Mr. Hayamizu couldn't step on the gas.

317
00:18:24,734 --> 00:18:27,434
But, they just said that the car wasn't rigged in any way just now.

318
00:18:27,434 --> 00:18:29,934
The car wasn't.

319
00:18:29,934 --> 00:18:33,434
Another place was rigged.

320
00:18:34,534 --> 00:18:36,834
-Ran! -Oh, yes!

321
00:18:44,934 --> 00:18:47,034
It's the same as a road sign

322
00:18:47,034 --> 00:18:50,534
and reflective plate is pasted on it.

323
00:18:50,534 --> 00:18:51,834
It is normally positioned,

324
00:18:51,834 --> 00:18:53,934
so that it faces the direction in which Mr. Hayamizu's car came from

325
00:18:53,934 --> 00:18:57,034
and it stands out when light is shined on it.

326
00:18:57,034 --> 00:19:00,234
The glare does strain the eyes.

327
00:19:00,234 --> 00:19:02,134
I'm pretty sure that Mr. Kurumatani

328
00:19:02,134 --> 00:19:05,734
had changed the direction the sign faced beforehand.

329
00:19:05,734 --> 00:19:09,134
If so, the light that reflects from the sign

330
00:19:09,134 --> 00:19:11,634
will shine on Mr. Hayamizu's car.

331
00:19:11,634 --> 00:19:15,634
I wonder why we didn't notice it

332
00:19:15,634 --> 00:19:17,234
when we saw the image on the surveillance camera?

333
00:19:17,234 --> 00:19:20,434
It was outside the visual range of the surveillance camera,

334
00:19:20,434 --> 00:19:23,434
it wasn't in view.

335
00:19:23,434 --> 00:19:26,134
After leaving the convenience store,

336
00:19:26,134 --> 00:19:28,434
Mr. Hayamizu's car headed for this intersection

337
00:19:28,434 --> 00:19:30,634
using the road alongside the irrigation channel.

338
00:19:30,634 --> 00:19:34,034
At the intersection, he had the right of way,

339
00:19:34,034 --> 00:19:38,134
so he drove straight without slowing down.

340
00:19:38,134 --> 00:19:39,634
Just about that time,

341
00:19:39,634 --> 00:19:42,034
the light that reflected on the sign,

342
00:19:42,034 --> 00:19:43,034
was at an angle that shined a little

343
00:19:43,034 --> 00:19:45,734
in the foreground of the intersection.

344
00:19:45,734 --> 00:19:49,334
Not aware of this, Mr. Hayamizu approached the intersection.

345
00:19:52,934 --> 00:19:54,134
What the...

346
00:20:06,934 --> 00:20:09,134
Mr. Hayamizu was surprised at the blinding light

347
00:20:09,134 --> 00:20:11,834
and failed to step on the brakes.

348
00:20:11,834 --> 00:20:14,834
Moreover, because of the after image of the reflected light,

349
00:20:14,834 --> 00:20:18,034
Mr. Kurumatani's car wasn't found.

350
00:20:18,034 --> 00:20:20,934
He probably picked 14:00 as the time to meet at the convenience store,

351
00:20:20,934 --> 00:20:24,134
taking into consideration the angle of the sun.

352
00:20:24,134 --> 00:20:26,834
Could it be that he crashed into the sign

353
00:20:26,834 --> 00:20:28,934
to cover up the fact that he changed directions?

354
00:20:28,934 --> 00:20:31,934
It's most likely that you crashed into Mr. Hayamizu's car

355
00:20:31,934 --> 00:20:33,834
on the driver's seat side.

356
00:20:35,534 --> 00:20:38,934
I actually wanted to crash into that guy directly.

357
00:20:38,934 --> 00:20:44,034
-Huh? -Hayamizu hit-and-run my little sister a year ago.

358
00:20:44,034 --> 00:20:45,434
What?

359
00:20:45,434 --> 00:20:46,734
Six months ago,

360
00:20:46,734 --> 00:20:50,534
I realized when a red foreign car came in for a tune up.

361
00:20:50,534 --> 00:20:55,434
Ever since then, all I thought about is avenging her death.

362
00:20:55,434 --> 00:20:59,234
Hayamizu brought that car in again for a tune up.

363
00:20:59,234 --> 00:21:02,834
That's why I planned what I did.

364
00:21:02,834 --> 00:21:04,434
I urged him to turn himself into the police

365
00:21:04,434 --> 00:21:06,934
when he came to return the car.

366
00:21:06,934 --> 00:21:10,034
But, he insisted on playing dumb,

367
00:21:10,034 --> 00:21:12,734
so I went on with my plan.

368
00:21:13,934 --> 00:21:15,134
If he only turned himself in,

369
00:21:15,134 --> 00:21:20,834
I would've at least spared him his life, that rat.

370
00:21:20,834 --> 00:21:21,934
You're just as much a rat yourself

371
00:21:21,934 --> 00:21:25,434
if you keep quiet about the fact

372
00:21:25,434 --> 00:21:28,234
that you planned an accident to kill Mr. Hayamizu.

373
00:21:28,234 --> 00:21:30,634
Now's your turn to turn yourself in.

374
00:21:35,934 --> 00:21:40,534
Mr. Detective, when did you realize my scheme?

375
00:21:40,534 --> 00:21:45,334
When you said you didn't notice the rainbow.

376
00:21:46,334 --> 00:21:48,134
The collision course phenomenon cannot happen

377
00:21:48,134 --> 00:21:50,934
unless the driver is looking ahead.

378
00:21:50,934 --> 00:21:53,534
You didn't notice the rainbow,

379
00:21:53,534 --> 00:21:55,534
because you were so absorbed in wanting to hit Mr. Hayamizu's car

380
00:21:55,534 --> 00:21:59,134
that you were looking only to the side, isn't that right?

381
00:22:00,134 --> 00:22:03,134
If you keep on harboring feelings of grudge and hate,

382
00:22:03,134 --> 00:22:05,234
you'll lose sight of the beautiful things

383
00:22:05,234 --> 00:22:08,234
right in front of your eyes.

384
00:23:32,934 --> 00:23:35,234
Dad, it's dangerous to speed so much

385
00:23:35,234 --> 00:23:36,634
when you didn't get enough sleep.

386
00:23:36,634 --> 00:23:40,034
I'm fine. My head's cleared up.

387
00:23:40,034 --> 00:23:43,234
I guess so, after all you did get some sleep.

388
00:23:43,234 --> 00:23:44,734
We've got to return the rental car tonight

389
00:23:44,734 --> 00:23:47,734
or we'll have to pay extension fee, don't we?

390
00:23:47,734 --> 00:23:50,134
But, everything will be in vain if we get into an accident, you know.

391
00:23:50,134 --> 00:23:51,434
I'm fine...

392
00:23:51,434 --> 00:23:55,434
Besides, I've got a mahjong game tonight

393
00:23:55,434 --> 00:23:57,834
and the prize is Yoko-chan's premium DVD!

394
00:23:57,834 --> 00:24:01,034
I'll be there soon, Yoko-chan!

395
00:24:01,034 --> 00:24:04,434
This is what you call, Kogoro phenomenon. He never learns.

396
00:24:06,334 --> 00:24:09,434
"Next Episode" -The yawning girl with those unpleasing eyes.

397
00:24:09,434 --> 00:24:12,534
I'm so sorry.

398
00:24:12,534 --> 00:24:14,534
That I'm the yawning girl with unpleasing eyes.

399
00:24:16,634 --> 00:24:18,434
The car that you hitchhiked on

400
00:24:18,434 --> 00:24:20,634
was that of bad people?

401
00:24:20,634 --> 00:24:23,534
I wonder who these two are?

402
00:24:23,534 --> 00:24:27,734
What if they're men from the Black Organization?

403
00:24:27,734 --> 00:24:30,934
They may virtually kill us. Kill us all together?

404
00:24:30,934 --> 00:24:32,334
Next Conan,

405
